      In times of misinformation, fake news, mass surveillance and political propaganda, science must be freed from corporate monopolies. Scientists, researchers, academics and their related organizations must have control over the medium where their work is published, reviewed, shared, read and discussed.<br/>
      The OpenScience Network is developing open digital spaces that address the most urgent priorities in open science communities.<br/>
      By leveraging a federated digital space, communities will be able to draft papers, browse contextual articles, engage in meaningful discussions and collaborate with other scientists without being siloed in walled gardens or engaged in dark patterns. Scientific discoveries will be vetted, put in perspective and linked to prior work. <br />
